    <h1><b><center>The Ultimate 7-Day Workout Plan for Weight Loss</center></b></h1>
    <h2><b>Introduction</b></h2>
    <h2><b>Day 1:</b></h2>
    <h2><i>High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)</i></h2>
    <p> HIIT involves short bursts of intense exercise followed by brief periods of rest. This approach is effective for burning calories and boosting metabolism.
        
        Warm-up: 5 minutes of jogging or jumping jCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <metacks
        
        Workout:
        
        30 seconds of sprinting
        
        30 seconds of rest
        
        Repeat for 20 minutes
        
        
        Cool-down: 5 minutes of stretching</p>
        <h2><b>Day 2:</b></h2>
        <h2><i>Strength Training (Upper Body Focus)</i></h2>
           <p> Building muscle increases the body’s resting metabolic rate, helping to burn more calories.
            
            Warm-up: 5 minutes of dynamic stretching
            
            Workout:
            
            Push-ups – 3 sets of 12 reps
            
            Dumbbell bench press – 3 sets of 10 reps
            
            Bent-over rows – 3 sets of 10 reps
            
            Plank – 3 sets of 30 seconds
            
            
            Cool-down: 5 minutes of stretching</p>
            <h2><b>Day 3:</b></h2>
            <h2><i> Cardio (Steady-State)</i></h2>
               <p> Moderate-intensity cardio improves heart health and fat-burning efficiency.
                
                Warm-up: 5 minutes of walking
                
                Workout: 30–45 minutes of jogging or cycling at a steady pace
                
                Cool-down: 5 minutes of walking and stretching</p>
                <h2><b>Day 4:</b></h2>
                <h2><i>Strength Training (Lower Body Focus)</i></h2>
                  <p>  Targeting large muscle groups in the legs boosts overall strength and fat burning.
                    
                    Warm-up: 5 minutes of dynamic stretching
                    
                    Workout:
                    
                    Squats – 3 sets of 12 reps
                    
                    Deadlifts – 3 sets of 10 reps
                    
                    Lunges – 3 sets of 10 reps per leg
                    
                    Glute bridges – 3 sets of 12 reps
                    
                    
                    Cool-down: 5 minutes of stretching</p>
                    <h2><b>Day 5:</b></h2>
                    <h2> <i>Active Recovery (Yoga or Light Stretching)</i></h2>
                       <p> Active recovery promotes muscle repair and reduces the risk of injury.
                        
                        20–30 minutes of yoga or light stretching</p>
                      <h2><b>Day 6:</b></h2>     
                      <h2><i> HIIT (Full Body Focus)</i></h2>
                        <p> strength and cardio enhances fat burning and overall fitness.
                        
                        Warm-up: 5 minutes of jumping jacks
                        
                        Workout:
                        
                        Burpees – 30 seconds
                        
                        Mountain climbers – 30 seconds
                        
                        Rest – 30 seconds
                        
                        Repeat for 20 minutes
                        
                        
                        Cool-down: 5 minutes of stretching </p>
                        <h2><b>Day 7:</b></h2> 
                        <h2> <i>Low-Intensity Steady-State Cardio (LISS)</i></h2>
                           <p> LISS helps with fat oxidation and muscle recovery.
                            
                            Workout: 30–45 minutes of brisk walking or light cycling </p> 
